data.chText: much、 a lot of和many的最高级
data.enText: used as the superlative of ‘much’, ‘a lot of’, ‘many’

data.chText: （数量上）最多，最大
data.enText: the largest in number or amount

data.chText: 你认为谁会得到最多的选票？
data.enText: Who do you think will get (the) most votes?

data.chText: 在这些人当中，她最有钱。
data.enText: She had the most money of all of them.

data.chText: 我在第一个问题上花的时间最多。
data.enText: I spent most time on the first question.

data.chText: 谁吃得最多？
data.enText: Who ate the most?

data.chText: 主任可能会损失最大。
data.enText: The director has the most to lose .

data.text: The can be left out in informal
在非正式英国英语中，the可以省略。

data.chText: 大多数；几乎所有
data.enText: more than half of sb/sth; almost all of sb/sth

data.chText: 几乎什么蔬菜我都喜欢。
data.enText: I like most vegetables.

data.chText: 大多数古典音乐都会让我睡着。
data.enText: Most classical music sends me to sleep.

data.chText: 你们大多数人都知道，我已经决定辞职了。
data.enText: As most of you know, I've decided to resign.

data.chText: 我邀请的人多半都来了。
data.enText: Most of the people I had invited turned up.

data.chText: 英语有数千个动词，大多数是规则动词。
data.enText: There are thousands of verbs in English and most (of them) are regular.

data.text: The is not used with most in this meaning.

data.enText: at (the) most

data.chText: 至多；不超过
data.enText: not more than

data.chText: 作为一则新闻，它至多只能占一小段。
data.enText: As a news item it merits a short paragraph at most.

data.chText: 那儿最多只有50个人。
data.enText: There were 50 people there, at the very most.

data.chText: （与两个或两个以上音节的形容词或副词连用，构成最高级）最
data.enText: used to form the superlative of adjectives and adverbs of two or more syllables

data.chText: 最烦人的 / 最美丽的部分
data.enText: the most boring/beautiful part

data.chText: 最没钱的人最慷慨大方。
data.enText: It was the people with the least money who gave most generously.

data.text: When most is followed only by an adverb, the is not used:

data.enText: This reason is mentioned most frequently
This is the most frequently mentioned reason

data.text: most 后只接副词时不用 the： This reason is mentioned most frequently，但要说 This is the most frequently mentioned reason。

data.chText: （程度上）最大，最多，最高
data.enText: to the greatest degree

data.chText: 你最欣赏的是什么？
data.enText: What did you enjoy (the) most?

data.chText: 这就是她最想得到的。
data.enText: It was what she wanted most of all .

data.text: The is often left out in informal English.
在非正式英语中，the常常省略。

data.chText: 非常；极其；完全
data.enText: very; extremely; completely

data.chText: 你来接我真是太好了。
data.enText: It was most kind of you to meet me.

data.chText: 我们极有可能再也见不到面了。
data.enText: We shall most probably never meet again.

data.chText: 这项技术看上去简单，但绝不是那么回事。
data.enText: This technique looks easy, but it most certainly is not.

data.chText: 几乎；差不多
data.enText: almost

data.chText: 我几乎每天都去商店。
data.enText: I go to the store most every day.

means: (与两个或两个以上音节的形容词或副词连用，构成最高级)最

data.enText: at (the) most

data.chText: 至多；不超过
data.enText: not more than

data.chText: 作为一则新闻，它至多只能占一小段。
data.enText: As a news item it merits a short paragraph at most.

data.chText: 那儿最多只有50个人。
data.enText: There were 50 people there, at the very most.

tr: (of actions or states) slightly short of or not quite accomplished
example: the baby was almost asleep when the alarm sounded
the car all but ran her down
virtually all the parties signed the contract
I was near exhausted by the run
the king cobra is the most dangerous snake

value.def: You use most to refer to the majority of a group of things or people or the largest part of something.

example.ex: Most of the houses in the capital don't have piped water...
example.tran: 首都的大部分房屋没有自来水。

example.ex: By stopping smoking you are undoing most of the damage smoking has caused...
example.tran: 通过戒烟可以消除吸烟造成的大部分危害。

example.ex: Sadly, most of the house was destroyed by fire in 1828.
example.tran: 遗憾的是，这座房屋在1828年的火灾中大部分被烧毁。

example.ex: Most people think the Queen has done a good job over the last 50 years...
example.tran: 多数人认为女王在过去50年间的表现令人满意。

example.ex: Most companies are looking to sponsor students on specific courses.
example.tran: 大部分公司在寻求机会资助学习某些特定课程的学生。

example.ex: Seventeen civilians were hurt. Most are students who had been attending a twenty-first birthday party...
example.tran: 17名平民受伤，大部分是学生，在参加一个21岁生日聚会。

example.ex: All of the rooms have private baths, and most have radios and TV.
example.tran: 所有房间都自带浴室，大部分房间有收音机和电视机。

value.def: You use the most to mean a larger amount than anyone or anything else, or the largest amount possible.

example.ex: The President himself won the most votes...
example.tran: 总统本人获得最多选票。

example.ex: The skippers get the most money, and after them the cooks...
example.tran: 船长拿到的钱最多，其次是厨师。

example.ex: Tom had the most authority of all.
example.tran: 汤姆在所有人中威信最高。

example.ex: The most they earn in a day is ten roubles.
example.tran: 他们每天最多挣10卢布。

value.def: You use most to indicate that something is true or happens to a greater degree or extent than anything else.

example.ex: What she feared most was becoming like her mother...
example.tran: 她最怕的就是变得像她妈妈那样。

example.ex: What they wanted most from the president was a leader who at least would try to educate the country.
example.tran: 他们对总统最大的期待是，至少他应尽力教诲国民。

example.ex: ...Professor Morris, the person he most hated.
example.tran: 莫里斯教授，他最憎恶的人

defx.def: You use most of all to indicate that something happens or is true to a greater extent than anything else.

example.ex: She said she wanted most of all to be fair.
example.tran: 她说她最想要的是公平。

value.def: You use most to indicate that someone or something has a greater amount of a particular quality than most other things of its kind.

example.ex: Her children had the best, most elaborate birthday parties in the neighborhood...
example.tran: 她的孩子们的生日聚会在街坊四邻里是最好、最讲究的。

example.ex: He was one of the most influential performers of modern jazz...
example.tran: 他是现代爵士乐最有影响力的表演者之一。

example.ex: If anything, swimming will appeal to her most strongly...
example.tran: 如果说有什么能强烈地吸引她，那就是游泳了。

example.ex: Keeping pace with the litter during summer, when the park is most heavily used, is also a huge task.
example.tran: 夏季公园游人最多的时候，及时清扫废弃物也是一项艰巨的任务。

example.ex: ...the most junior of the New York Times music critics.
example.tran: 《纽约时报》最年轻的乐评人

value.def: If you do something the most, you do it to the greatest extent possible or with the greatest frequency.

example.ex: What question are you asked the most?...
example.tran: 你们被问及最多的问题是什么？

example.ex: Inevitably those who suffer the most are the mothers and children...
example.tran: 妇女和儿童必然是最遭罪的。

example.ex: Among the subjects for which the pass rate has risen the most are art and design, business studies, and music.
example.tran: 及格率提高最多的科目是艺术设计、商业研究和音乐。

value.tran: 最大限度地;最频繁地;最多地

value.def: You use most in conversations when you want to draw someone's attention to something very interesting or important that you are about to say.

example.ex: Most surprisingly, quite a few said they don't intend to vote at all...
example.tran: 最让人吃惊的是，相当多的人说他们根本不打算参加投票。

example.ex: Most interestingly, they are  demanding that a national working party on crimes against women and children be established.
example.tran: 最令人关注的是，他们要求针对侵害妇女和儿童的犯罪成立全国专案组。

value.tran: (在谈话中用于引起注意)最…，极其…

value.def: You use most to emphasize an adjective or adverb.

example.ex: I'll be most pleased to speak to them...
example.tran: 能跟他们谈谈我会十分高兴。

example.ex: I believe he is most painfully anxious about Diana.
example.tran: 我相信他肯定非常担心黛安娜。

value.boxu_tran: 注意可以说：Most children love sweets（大多数孩子爱吃糖果），但不能说Most of children love sweets;如果使用代词，则可以说 Most of them love sweets（他们大多数爱吃糖果）。
value.boxu_usage: Note that you can say 'Most children love sweets', but you cannot say 'Most of children love sweets'. However, when a pronoun is used, you can say 'Most of them love sweets'.

value.def: You use at most or at the most to say that a number or amount is the maximum that is possible and that the actual number or amount may be smaller.

example.ex: Poach the pears in apple juice for perhaps ten minutes at most.
example.tran: 把梨放入苹果汁中，最多煮10分钟左右。

example.ex: ...staying on at school for two extra years to study only three, or at the most four subjects...
example.tran: 在学校再多呆两年学习仅仅三门、至多四门课程

example.ex: Many companies are expecting flat sales or at most a 1 to 2 percent increase over last year.
example.tran: 很多公司预计销售不会有大的起色，或者最多比去年增多1%或2%。

value.def: If you make the most of something, you get the maximum use or advantage from it.

example.ex: Happiness is the ability to make the most of what you have...
example.tran: 幸福就是有能力充分享受你拥有的一切。

example.ex: Making the most of your hair means getting the cut and shape right.
example.tran: 让头发达到最佳效果意味着要修剪得当，并选择合适的发型。

usage_note.note: Most is often considered to be the superlative form of much and many.
usage_note.translation: most 常被认为是 much 和 many 的最高级。

trans: 重要的；有重大影响的；有巨大价值的；影响很大的；权威的
多数人；绝大多数人；人们；大部分人；大多数人
最受欢迎的；最得人心的；最普遍的
可能的，有希望的( likely的最高级 )；适合的
不论怎样说；在大多数情况下；一般地
最可能；最有可能；最可几；最概然；最可能的
对大多数（实用）场合来说，在很多（实际）场合
（对大主教的尊称）最尊敬的大主教大人
